column5: SURVEY INTRODUCTION To assure data consistency and accuracy, PIT Count team members MUST read this introduction verbatim to all unsheltered persons prior to conducting survey. Thank you. --- Hi, my name is ________. I'm an outreach volunteer/worker. We are trying to understand who is out here tonight so we can do a better job of providing services. Are you sleeping here/outside tonight? Would you be willing to answer a few questions? It will take about five minutes. You can skip any questions you don't want to answer and still get the bus pass. What you tell me will not be used to identify you.  --- I have read aloud, to the persons surveyed, the exact language in the Survey Introduction.
